# Cloudflare Pages custom-headers file. Docusaurus copies static/** verbatim
# into the deploy artifact, so this ships at the site root as /_headers.
# Post-deploy check: `curl -sI https://agent-assembly.com/ | grep -iE 'content-security-policy|x-frame-options'`
# must return the corresponding header lines. If they are absent, the deploy
# workflow (deploy.yml -> Cloudflare Pages) did not pick up static/_headers.
#
# script-src allows static.cloudflareinsights.com: Cloudflare Web Analytics
# auto-injects its beacon.min.js from that host on this Pages-proxied site, so
# without it the beacon trips a policy violation. Its telemetry POST goes to the
# same-origin /cdn-cgi/rum endpoint, already covered by connect-src 'self'. The
# report stream was confirmed clean, so this is the cutover to an enforcing
# Content-Security-Policy (AAASM-4884); it is no longer Report-Only.
/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' www.googletagmanager.com static.cloudflareinsights.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; connect-src 'self' www.google-analytics.com www.googletagmanager.com; img-src 'self' data: https:; font-src 'self' data:; frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self'
